    {
      "id": "s1_general",
      "number": 1,
      "title": "General information",
      "indicator_icon": "circle",
      "interpretation": "How to interpret your answers: ↑ likelihood for good welfare (top/left) → ↑ risk for compromised welfare (bottom/right). For colourblind people, the answer options accompanied with icons are arranged in order from most optimal to least desired, either from top to bottom or from left to right. 🔍 Observe: an opportunity to learn more about your parrot's behaviours and needs. This includes observing your bird in daily life, either directly or via camera, reflecting on the care, environment, and daily interactions you provide. Seeking guidance from appropriately qualified professionals is highly recommended. An avian veterinarian or a certified parrot behavioural consultant can help review your assessment results and, if needed, develop an effective plan to improve your parrot's welfare.",
